pr_body:
This PR aims to replace all the data views in navidrome to use infinite scroll as part of GSoC ([project](https://github.com/navidrome/navidrome/pull/1258)). 

It implements the following -

### 1. Custom Infinitely scrolling Datagrid
Implements a custom react admin DataGrid which supports infinite scroll. It is designed to work as a drop in replacement for Datagrid and List. It implements dynamic columns, filter, sort, selections etc. It doesn't however implement `expand` which is planned to be removed in https://github.com/navidrome/navidrome/pull/1258

**How to use**
```js
import { Datagrid, List } from './infiniteScroll';

<List {...props}>
     <Datagrid>
            {/* Fields */}
     </Datagrid>
</List>
```

This custom control replaces the existing Datagrid in `ArtistList`, `AlbumList`, `SongList` and `PlaylistList`

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2987087/129885902-fe6b6533-e594-48a3-a34e-d27f3aa90012.mov

### 2. Infinitely Scrolling AlbumDatagrid

The `AlbumGridView` is a custom control to display the albums as a grid in navidrome. This PR implements a sub-component AlbumDatagrid which is used to allow infinite scrolling in the Album Grid.

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2987087/129887890-b63d1ed4-4935-43a7-b862-166632b5fb70.mp4

### 3. Infinitely Scrolling SimpleList

On smaller screens, navidrome has a SimpleList control to render the items. This PR also incorporates the SimpleList to use infinite scrolling using a sub component called `VirtualList`.

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2987087/129888429-00ac8f8a-4f7b-4938-8c76-3890b7a0cc8c.mov


This is implemented in `SimpleList`, `ArtistSimpleList` and `SongSimpleList`.

### 4. Helpers

Along with the above, this PR also includes some helpers to create custom infinitely scrolling components built on top of react-admin and react-virtualized, for example the `VirtualTable` and `VirtualList`. The base for all the components is the `useVirtualizedData` hook, which helps fetch data in a way which is friendly to both react virtualized & react admin.


### Blog Posts
- [Part 1](https://samarsault.com/open-source/music/gsoc/GSoC-21-Navidrome/)
- [Part 2](https://samarsault.com/open-source/gsoc/GSoC-21-Navidrome-Part-2/)
- [Part 3](https://samarsault.com/open-source/gsoc/GSoC-21-Navidrome-3/)

In this case, there's no value called `year`, but `maxYear` in the record. It's not used for displaying, but for checking if its been loaded since react-virtualized gets the `cellData` from `record[dataKey]`. https://github.com/samarsault/navidrome/blob/f684c9f0357965afa24fafaca7515c07049a58b9/ui/src/infiniteScroll/VirtualTable.js#L60-L69", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 9, 21, 7, 4, 11, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'samarsault', 'type': 'User'}]
